history.content:
As your first upper division courses? Not exactly advisable to do both, considering both classes are significant ramp ups in terms of conceptual difficulty. 189 in particular (especially in recent semesters) relies on significant mathematical maturity, so it is strongly advised to do at least one of 126 or 127 (if not both) before doing 189. 

170 is fine to take as a first UD, and is a great choice because it'll also help you with interviewing.


You could take 189 without 126 and 127, but it's a risk depending on how the professor teaching the class structures the course.

As for taking both together, it sounds like a bad idea because both classes are not only heavy, but consistently so (not any weeks where either class will let up in terms of work); you could do just those two and a H/SS, but I'd say it is better to first take something like 126 or 127 to really ramp up your mathematical maturity before taking on 189.

children.subject: ^ I agree with the student response. Both are very challenging courses.

history.content:
I have been reading past piazza posts, but haven't come to a consensus answer. 

Given I have done well in Math 53/54, EE16A/B, and CS70, but have not taken 126, 127, or 134, would taking 170 + 189 + (P/NP) H/SS together be manageable/advisable? These would be my first upper division courses.

Thanks!
